      "content": "wait, i think i misunderstood your explanation. `executeTrade` doesn't return anything, it just takes the pointer and does work. the leak happens because the `ord` object was heap-allocated before it even got to `processOrder`.\n\ncan you show me exactly how to use `std::unique_ptr` in `processOrder` so the memory is managed automatically even if an exception is thrown? i need to make sure there are no hidden leaks lurking in the background when the system is under heavy load.",
